ftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Object\/isConnected(signal:callable:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" first to check for existing connections.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"callable"},{"text":"’s object is freed, the connection will be lost.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Examples with recommended syntax:"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Connecting signals is one of the most common operations in Godot and the API gives many options to do so, which are described further down. The code block below shows the recommended approach."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"[code skip-lint]Object.connect()","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":" or [code skip-lint]Signal.connect()"},{"type":"text","text":"?"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As seen above, the recommended method to connect signals is not ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Object\/connect(signal:callable:flags:)"},{"text":". The code block below shows the four options for connecting signals, using either this legacy method or the recommended ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Signal\/connect(callable:flags:)"},{"text":", and using either an implicit ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Callable","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or a manually defined one."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"While all options have the same outcome (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"button"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s [signal BaseButton.button_down] signal will be connected to "},{"t